latestPosts.caption:
A Name Written in Destiny ✨

Some stories are meant to be lived, not just watched. A year ago, we watched Hi Nanna and fell in love with the idea of having kids—especially a baby girl. Just a month later, life surprised us with the most beautiful blessing.

From the very beginning, we wished to name her Mahi, but we didn’t know who was on the way. As time passed, everyone around us predicted a boy, so we held back from choosing a nickname for our little girl.

And then, on the 9th day of Navratri, she arrived—our baby girl, our Mahi. That day, the divine form of Goddess Durga matha was Mahishasura Mardhini, a name that perfectly aligned with what we had unknowingly chosen. A pure coincidence? Or destiny at play?

To make it even more special, my brother, just like us, had also dreamt of naming her Mahi after watching Hi Nanna.

And today, as we hold her in our arms, we realize—some names aren’t just chosen; they are meant to be. Mahi was always meant to be ours. ❤️

#OurMahi #NameReveal #DestinedToBe #HiNannaToRealLife #nickname #hinanna #babygirl
